# Insights & Recommendations

## Key Findings

1. Top 3 clinics generate the highest churn revenue loss.
2. Arthroscopic procedure, spinal rehabilitation, therapeutic massage procedures account for the largest share of churn revenue.
3. Churn rate increases significantly during winter/spring months.
4. High-revenue clinics also experience the highest absolute revenue loss due to churn.

## Business Interpretation

- High churn revenue in top clinics suggests operational or service quality issues rather than demand problems.
- Seasonal churn indicates that patients may not return after short-term treatment cycles.
- Certain procedures attract one-time patients with low retention potential.

## Recommendations

1. Prioritize retention campaigns in high-revenue clinics to maximize ROI.
2. Tailor SMS campaigns to procedure type (spinal rehabilitation vs therapeutic massage ).
3. Introduce follow-up programs during high-risk churn periods.
4. Pilot the campaign with a 10â€“15% recovery rate before full rollout.
